# Serial Binary Adder

> [!word] Serial Binary Adder
> The serial binary adder is a sequential logic circuit that performs binary addition bit by bit, one per clock cycle.

![../60-Meta-Attachments/ee7eb5ca3cdc76769dc83d5b525b94ef.png](data:image/png;base64,)

- A Clock Signal is used to synchronise the input and the memory output

## Why is a Serial Binary Adder Needed

> [!info]
> If only [[61-Archive/20220318121918-full-adder|Full Adders]] are used
>
> - To form an _N-bit_ adder, _N numbers_ of [[61-Archive/20220318121918-full-adder|Full Adders]] are needed
> - If we can memorize the previously calculated $C_{out}$ and give it to the next bit addition as its $C_{in}$, then only one adder is needed.
>   ![[Pasted-image-20220318123648.png|Pasted image 20220318123648]]
